2891.Description:
Essentially, this is a script designed to enable module builders to Limit items by setting 2 values on the items as local variables. An example lies below, btu to actively use this script it need to be merged into the modules OnItemEquip event. Having re-read the Twilight Giants Novels by Troy Denning, I was wondering how to set up a longbow similiar to Tavis Burdun's.

Said longbow, more a less, is the example below.



int ABILITY_STRENGTH = 0; int ABILITY_DEXTERITY = 1; 
int ABILITY_CONSTITUTION = 2; 
int ABILITY_INTELLIGENCE = 3; 
int ABILITY_WISDOM = 4; 
int ABILITY_CHARISMA = 5; 

an Example Longbow, we'll call "Bear Driller" would be thusly 
AbilityTypeNeeded INT 0 (Strength is score required) 
AbilityScoreNeeded INT 20 (20 Points in Score are needed) 

Before the question arises: No.. it will not have adverse affects with the 
"AbilityTypeNeeded" defaulting to 0. Because likewise "AbilityScoreNeeded" will 
default to 0. Since NWN let's the score in any stat never drop below 3, this will not cause any issues.

