3536.Description:
//::////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//:: OnAreaTransitionClick for Door or Trigger, OnUsed for Placeable
//:: pr_transition
//::////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/*
 Transports PC and all associates within a reasonable distance (15 m) to the
 designated object. Set destination with Transition tab. OR create a waypoint
 with the same TAG as the calling object.

 The point of this script is to let players and their associates to move within
 an area, while retaining the "area transition" feeling: The screen fades to
 black, and the transition is not instantaneous.

 This is meant to go into a OnAreaTransitionClick slot of a Door or a Trigger.
 For a Door transition to show, remember to set transition target in Transition
 slot of its Poperties.

 Placeables can also be used to send PCs on their way: Set this script in the
 OnUsed slot of the placeable, and create a waypoint with the same tag as the
 placeable. Nice for ladders, trapdoors, etc.

 NB: If the calling object has no transition target, it searches for a waypoint
 with the same tag as itself. Doors that set each other as transition targets
 will get confused if waypoints with their tags exist, and go to these instead.
*/
//::////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//:: Peter Fryxelius, Sep 2008
//::////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

3538.Description:
//::////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//:: OnUsed script for Torch Bracket placeables (3 different)
//:: pr_torch
//::////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/*
 This script makes the standard NWN torch come to life. Adventurers can
 interact with torch brackets in many ways:
 - If bracket is empty and you wield a torch, place torch in bracket, lit.
 - If bracket has unlit torch, and you wield a torch, light up the one in
 bracket.
 - If bracket has unlit torch, and you wield no torch, take the torch to your
 inventory.
 - If bracket has lit torch, and you wield a torch, extinguish bracket torch.
 - If bracket has lit torch, and you wield no torch, take it into hand.

 Placeables are found in: Custom / Dungeon* / Lighting*. Note that Torch MOUNT
 variants are the CEP creations, these (useable ones) are the Torch BRACKETS.
*/
//::////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//:: Peter Fryxelius, Sep 2008
//::////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

